cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification (ReID), which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel knowledge distillation method, which involves training a model to mimic the representations of multiple partial ReID models. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the security implications of ReID, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
